data.title: Pixar Animation Studios
data.meta_description: Pixar began in 1979 as The Graphics Group, a part of the computer division of Lucasfilm. On February 3, 1986, Apple Computer co-founder Steve Jobs acquired the company from Lucasfilm and renamed it Pixar.
